# Data Layer: Repositories + Mappers

## 1) Repository implementations belong to `*-data`
- Domain contracts (e.g. `interface *Repository`) must be implemented in the corresponding `*-data` module (e.g. `*RepositoryImpl`).
- `*-data` must not depend on UI or Compose.

## 2) Mapping rules (DataDTO/Entity -> Domain entity)
- Mapping from:
  - `*-data-network` network entities -> `common/persistence` storage entities -> `*-domain` domain entities
  - must be done in `*-data` via dedicated mappers (e.g. `*DataMapper.kt`).
- Domain must not leak persistence/network types:
  - methods in `*-data` returning domain entities must return only domain entities (`*DD` / domain models).

## 3) Delegation of IO and threading
- `*-data` repository implementations should delegate IO to:
  - `*-data-network` data sources (they wrap HTTP in `withContext(dispatcherProvider.IO)`)
  - `common/persistence/persistence-database` storage (it uses `DatabaseCreator` with `dispatcherProvider.IO`)
- If `*-data` does any extra blocking work, wrap it with the shared dispatcher abstraction (via your `DispatcherProvider`), not `Dispatchers.IO` directly.

## 4) Concurrency must be structured
- Use structured concurrency (e.g. `coroutineScope`, `supervisorScope`) and avoid `GlobalScope`.
- If you fetch a batch in parallel, prefer:
  - `supervisorScope { async { ... } }`
  - per-item failure handling (so one failure doesn’t cancel the whole batch unless required).

## 5) Error semantics: when to swallow vs propagate
- Decide explicitly per operation:
  - “Best-effort refresh”: swallow per-item exceptions (e.g. turn failed items into `null` and `mapNotNull`), so use-cases can still complete successfully.
  - “Operation must fail”: do not swallow; let exceptions propagate so `SuspendUseCase` / `FlowUseCase` can convert them to `Resource.Error` for UI.
- Avoid broad try/catch around the whole repository method unless the behavior is intended and documented.

## 6) DI registration
- Register repository implementations in `*-data` as small Koin modules.
- Use explicit bindings like:
  - `factoryOf(::SomeRepositoryImpl) bind SomeRepository::class`

